25/02/2011
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Hundreds of protestors organised via Facebook gathered in downtown Zagreb on Thursday (February 24th) for an anti-government rally, which ended with police clashes. 
The demonstrators, as many as 1,000 according to organisers and 300 according to police, demanded the resignation of Prime Minister Jadranka Kosor's government over alleged corruption. 
Local media reported that the clashes resulted in several injuries and 11 arrests. 
(Hina, HRT, Novi List - 24/02/11)
